<p><a name="On_Italian_Corporatism" id="On_Italian_Corporatism"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Corporatism&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: On Italian Corporatism">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">On Italian Corporatism</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://sources.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constitution_of_Fiume" class="external text" title="http://sources.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constitution_of_Fiume" rel="nofollow">Constitution of Fiume</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.vatican.va/holy_father/leo_xiii/encyclicals/documents/hf_l-xiii_enc_15051891_rerum-novarum_en.html" class="external text" title="http://www.vatican.va/holy_father/leo_xiii/encyclicals/documents/hf_l-xiii_enc_15051891_rerum-novarum_en.html" rel="nofollow"><i>Rerum Novarum</i>: encyclical of Pope Leo XIII on capital and labor</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.vatican.va/holy_father/pius_xi/encyclicals/documents/hf_p-xi_enc_19310515_quadragesimo-anno_en.html" class="external text" title="http://www.vatican.va/holy_father/pius_xi/encyclicals/documents/hf_p-xi_enc_19310515_quadragesimo-anno_en.html" rel="nofollow"><i>Quadragesimo Anno</i>: encyclical of Pope Pius XI on reconstruction of the social order</a></li>
<li>There is an essay on "The Doctrine of Fascism" credited to <a href="/wiki/Benito_Mussolini" title="Benito Mussolini">Benito Mussolini</a> that appeared in the 1932 edition of the <i>Enciclopedia Italiana</i>, and excerpts can be read at <a href="/wiki/Doctrine_of_Fascism" title="Doctrine of Fascism" class="mw-redirect">Doctrine of Fascism</a>. There are also links there to the complete text.</li>
</ul>
